    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Put a large baking tray (or two!) in the oven to heat up (this will stop your <strong>pizza bottoms</strong> from going soggy!)</p><p>Add your <strong>tomato paste </strong>to a bowl with your <strong>dried oregano</strong> and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Add 5 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[7 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [10 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato base</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-broccoli-pizza/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>soft cheese</strong> to a separate bowl with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Mix<strong> </strong>it all together<strong> </strong>until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy base</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-broccoli-pizza/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain your <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-broccoli-pizza/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> in half lengthways</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-broccoli-pizza/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the heated tray[s] from the oven and add the<strong> pizza bases</strong></p><p>Divide the <strong>tomato base</strong> between the <strong>pizza bases</strong> and spread it evenly all over them with the back of a spoon</p><p>Dollop the<strong> creamy base</strong> over the pizza bases and lightly swirl into the tomato base</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-broccoli-pizza/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top the bases with the<strong> torn mozzarella</strong></p><p>Tear over your <strong>'Nduja</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Top with the<strong> chopped Tenderstem broccoli </strong>and add a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-broccoli-pizza/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 13-15 min or until the cheese has melted and the bases are crisp</p><p>Once the pizzas are cooked, remove from the oven \u2013 these are your<strong> creamy 'Nduja & broccoli pizzas</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-broccoli-pizza/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy 'Nduja & broccoli pizzas</strong> seasoned with a generous pinch of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
